about the community housing office student housing search search this site stanford university student housing housing options apply for housing moving in moving out living in housing calendar home community housing about the community housing office the community housing office is the primary office at stanford university that provides information about housing opportunities in the stanford area the office is open year round and listings are available to students staff faculty and visiting scholars and researchers please not that listings are places through places4students services we offer assistance in wording your listing for maximum effectiveness referral to landlord tenant and mediation services advantages to listing your property through the stanford university section of the places4students web site fast turnaround listings are updated on all non holiday weekdays prospective tenants can view listings at any time listings are available on the web 24 hours a day listings allow generous space for describing amenities high quality pool of prospective tenants target audience approximately 15700 students approximately 4800 of whom will live off campus 43 of graduate students live off campus 4 of undergraduate students live off campus 1000 postdoctoral scholars 10000 staff members 1900 faculty members visiting scholars and researchers how to reach our office to place edit or remove a rental listing please go the the places4students web site or call their toll free number 866 766 0767 places4students is located on the eastern end of the continent near niagara falls the community housing office is located in the harold modular building at 630 serra street 110 between encina hall and the stanford eating clubs the office is open from 8 am to 5 pm monday through friday you may contact community housing by telephone 650 723 3906 e mail communityhousing stanford edu us mail 630 serra street 110 stanford ca 94305 fax 650 736 1297 coming to the office in person select here for directions from el camino real from highway 280 or from highway 101 select here for a map showing the location of our office the office is staffed by one full time employee for this reason it may at times be difficult to reach the office if you leave a message or send and e mail you will be contacted as soon as possible after the staff member returns or otherwise becomes available last modified tue 24 may 2011 at 16 24 printer friendly version all community housing student housing logo community housing about community housing directions get access to the housing listings housing listings how to submit a listing listing policies places 4 students community housing resources resources for finding housing housing types & cost short term visitors wheelchair access pets in apartments premises checklist tenant resume choosing a housemate buying furniture storage space rentals legal information faq about the stanford area local community stanford area housing city websites transportation and maps local hotels and motels academic calendar housing portal welcome home housing options apply for housing moving in moving out living in housing calendar about us contact us quick links general housing info axess fix it request help su mail & deliveries residence agreement termination of occupancy construction news housing front desks community housing stanford guest house faculty & staff housing residential & dining enterprises office of the senior associate vice provost for r&de stanford dining stanford hospitality & auxiliaries stanford conferences student housing site map share this student housing is a division of residential & dining enterprises the residential & dining enterprises logo
